TOKYO, March 8 (Xinhua) -- Japan's composite index of coincident economic indicators for January fell 3.0 points from the previous month, the Cabinet Office said Wednesday. According to the Cabinet Office's preliminary report, the coincident index, which reflects current economic conditions, stood at 96.1 against the 2015 base of 100. A rise in the coincident index indicates an expansion of economic activity and a decline indicates a contraction. The leading index, a yardstick for the economy's performance months ahead, fell 0.4 point at 96.5.  â– 